			<font style="display: inline;">THE FIRST OF LONG ISLAND CORPORATION</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">10 Glen Head Road</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Glen Head, New York 11545</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">(516) 671-4900</font>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>

		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:200%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROXY STATEMENT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:200%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="InformationAboutAnnualMeetingofStckhldrs"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">INFORMATION ABOUT THE ANNUAL MEETING OF STOCKHOLDERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The accompanying proxy is being solicited by the Board of Directors (&#x201C;Board&#x201D;) of The First of Long Island Corporation (&#x201C;Corporation&#x201D; or &#x201C;Company&#x201D;) for use at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be held at 3:30 P.M. local time at </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">North Hempstead Country Club</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">291 Port Washington Blvd.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Port Washington</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, New York on April </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The approximate date on which proxy statements and forms of proxy are first being sent or given t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">o stockholders is March 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Proxies in the accompanying form that are properly executed and duly returned to the Corporation, or voted electronically, will be voted at the meeting </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in accordance with the instructions provided.&nbsp;&nbsp;Where no instructions are indicated, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">properly</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> executed proxies will be voted &#x201C;F</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x201D; the proposals set forth in this proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Each proxy granted may be revoked at any time prior to its exercise by written notice filed with the secretary of the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, by </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">submission of a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> later dated and executed proxy</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or by notice given during the meeting by the stockholder to the presiding officer of the meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;The presence in person or by proxy of the holders of a majority of the shares entitled to vote at the annual meeting constitutes a quorum for the transaction of business. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">meeting (whether or not a quorum is present) may be adjourned to a subsequent date, provided notice of the time and place to which the meeting is adjourned are announced at the meeting at which the adjournment is taken.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">At an adjourned meeting, any business may be transacted which might have been transacted at the meeting as originally scheduled.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">In the event there are not sufficient votes for a quorum, or to approve or ratify any matter being presented at the time of this Annual Meeting, the Annual Meeting may be adjourned in order to permit the further solicitation of proxies.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="VotingSecuritiesandPrincipalStckhldrs"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">VOTING SECURITIES AND PRINCIPAL STOCKHOLDERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The only class of voting securities of the Corporation is its Common Stock, $.10 par value ("Common Stock"), each share of which entitles the holder thereof to one vote except in the election of directors, where votes may be cumulated as described herein.&nbsp;&nbsp;Only stockholders of record at the close of business on </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">March 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> are entitled to notice of and to vote at the meeting. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">As of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">March 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, there were </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">153</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">936</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">shares of the Common Stock</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> issued</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, all of which were outstanding and entitled to vote.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the best knowledge of the Corporation, the only persons owning beneficially more than five percent (5%) of the Common Stock of the Corporation as of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">March 1, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> are identified in the table below. </font>
		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt 18pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="VotingProcedures"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">VOTING PROCEDURES AND METHODS OF COUNTING VOTES</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">As to Proposal 1 regarding the election of directors, the proxy card being provided by the Board enables a stockholder to vote &#x201C;For&#x201D; the election of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">six </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">nominees proposed by the Board or to &#x201C;Withhold Authority&#x201D; to vote for the nominees being proposed.&nbsp;&nbsp;As discussed under Proposal 1, cumulative voting applies to the election of directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;Directors are elected by a plurality of the votes cast, without regard to either broker non-votes or proxies as to which the authority to vote for the nominee is withheld.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">As to Proposals 2 and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, a stockholder may: (1) vote &#x201C;For&#x201D; the item, (2) vote &#x201C;Against&#x201D; the item, or (3) &#x201C;Abstain&#x201D; from voting on the item.&nbsp;&nbsp;In order to approve Proposals 2 and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">each proposal must receive the affirmative vote of a majority of the shares voting on each matter at the annual meeting without regard to either shares as to which the &#x201C;Abstain&#x201D; box is marked or broker non-votes.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Proxies solicited hereby will be returned to the Corporation, tabulated by the Corporation&#x2019;s registrar and transfer agent and reviewed by the inspectors of election designated by the Board.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"></font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Proposal1ElectionofDirectors"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROPOSAL 1</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">ELECTION OF DIRECTORS</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> FOR TWO YEAR TERMS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board of the Corporation currently consists of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">twelve </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">members.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he Board has nominated </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">John J. Desmond, Howard Thomas Hogan, Jr., Milbrey Rennie Taylor, Walter C. Teagle III and Michael N. Vittorio </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">as </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Class I directors for re-election</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Louisa M. Ives </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for election as a Class </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">I</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> director</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each Board member and nominee, with the exception of Michael N. Vittorio who serves as President and Chief Executive Officer (&#x201C;CEO&#x201D;) of the Corporation and its wholly owned bank subsidiary, The First National Bank of Long Island (&#x201C;Bank&#x201D;), is independent as defined in the Nasdaq Rules.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Arial Unicode MS;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board is divided into two classes, Class I and Class II.&nbsp;&nbsp;The following table sets forth the present composition of the Board.</font>
		</p>

				</td>
				<td valign="top" style="border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;width:27.24%;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

				</td>
			</tr>

					<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">As to the election of directors, each stockholder entitled to vote has the right to vote, in person or by proxy, the number of shares owned by him or her for as many persons as there are directors to be elected.&nbsp;&nbsp;A stockholder may also cumulate his or her votes by giving one candidate as many votes as the number of directors to be elected multiplied by the number of his or her shares or by </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">evenly </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">distributing such votes on the same principle among any number of candidates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Cumulative voting can affect the election of directors if there are more nominees for director than positions to be filled.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event that cumulative voting is in effect, it is the intention of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">proxies </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to vote cumulatively for the nominees listed, and if authority for any nominee or nominees is withheld, the votes will be distributed among the remaining candidates </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">at</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the discretion of the Board.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">It is intended that shares represented by properly executed proxies will be voted at the meeting in accordance with the instructions indicated thereon and, in the absence of contrary indication, for the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">re-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">election of d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">irectors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Desmond, Hogan, Taylor, Teagle and Vittorio </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the election of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">irector </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ives</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each of the Class </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">I</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> director</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> will hold office until his </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or her </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">successor is elected and qualified</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, except that it is expected that Mr. Vittorio, in accordance with the terms of his employment agreement, will discontinue his service as a director at the annual meeting of stockholders following the year ending December 31, 2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;If at the time of the 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting any of the nominees named above is unavailable or chooses not to serve as a director (an event that the Board does not now anticipate), the proxies will be voted for the election as director of such other person or persons as the Board may designate.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR all named nominees.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The following table sets forth a brief description of the business experience</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> during the past five years</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of each of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">nominees and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board members continuing in office</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;It also indicates any other directorships held during the past five years in any company with a class of securities registered pursuant to section 12 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934 (&#x201C;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1934 </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Act&#x201D;) or subject to the requirements of section 15(d) of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1934 </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Act or any company registered as an investment company under the Investment Company Act of 1940.&nbsp;&nbsp;The year set forth for each director is the year in which the person named became a director of the Corporation and the Bank with the exception of Mr. Hogan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> who became a director of the Corporation upon its formation in 198</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="QualificationsofDirectors"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">QUALIFICATIONS OF DIRECTORS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Diversity</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Governance and Nominating Committee believes that the Board as a whole should adequately reflect the diversity of the Company&#x2019;s constituencies and the communities in which the Company conducts business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although the Committee considers diversity in identifying nominees for director, it does not have a formal policy in this regard.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Committee has a broad view of diversity, and conceptualizes it to include differences of viewpoint, professional experience, education, skill and other individual qualities and attributes that contribute to board heterogeneity, as well as race, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ethnicity, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">gender, and other characteristics. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Specific Core Competencies</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition to general qualifications and the consideration of diversity, the Governance and Nominating Committee has developed a Skill Sets Matrix</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">that sets forth the specific core competencies it believes one or more Board members should possess.&nbsp;&nbsp;The matrix is used to evaluate the collective skills of the existing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">B</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oard and identify the skills that the Committee should seek when filling a Board vacancy or increasing the size of the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Governance and Nominating Committee recognizes that some Board members may possess many of the core competencies, while others will possess only a few,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">but that each Board member should have particular strength with respect to at least one.&nbsp;&nbsp;The identified core competencies, which are </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">subject to change from time to time, include, but are not limited to: </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">corporate governance, banking, strategic planning, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">business leadership, organizational management </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">/or</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> business operations, ac</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">counting and reporting, finance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and/</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or investments</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">technology </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and/</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or information security, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">mergers and acquisitions, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">legal </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and/</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or regulatory</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, real estate, marketing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and/</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> public relations </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">financial accounting </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">experience necessary to qualify as an &#x201C;audit committee financial expert&#x201D; as defined in Regulation S-K of the Securities and Exchange Commission</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> (&#x201C;SEC&#x201D;)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">With respect to each of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x2019;s directors, the narrative that follows sets forth the specific experience, qualifications, attributes and skills that led to the conclusion that the person should serve as a director </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">considering</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Company&#x2019;s business and structure and the general qualifications and core competencies identified and deemed desirable by the Governance and Nominating Committee.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Paul T. Canarick - </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Can</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">arick joined the Board in 1992 and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">is a member of the Governance and Nominating, Loan and Asset Liability Committees.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Canarick is President and Principal of Paul Todd, Inc., a privately held construction company.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Canarick&#x2019;s experience has provided him with a number of the core competencies identified by the Governance and Nominating Committee, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">which include </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">banking, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">business leadership, organizational management and business operations and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">real estate.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Alexander L. Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Chairman of the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;He is currently</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Chairman of Upc Switzerland and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Chief Executive Officer</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of Upc</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Central </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and Eastern </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Europe, Liberty Global plc</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Prior to that he was </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Chief Executive Officer</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, Central Europe Group, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Liberty Global</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> plc;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Chief Executive Officer, Austria/Switzerland </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Region</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">L</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">iberty Global </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">plc</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; and Chief Executive Officer, upc cablecom GmbH of Switzerland</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Tveter has extensive knowledge and experience in the US, UK and European cable industries.&nbsp;&nbsp;He was President of UK cable operator Telewest Global Inc. and held a range of senior management positions at Time Warner Cable, Comcast Corporation and Cablevision Systems Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Tveter </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">also</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> served as Chairman of Sightspeed </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Inc.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, a video conferencing and communications provider.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Tveter&#x2019;s experience has provided him with a number of the core competencies identified by the Governance and Nominating Committee, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">which include </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">corporate governance, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">banking, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">strategic planning, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">business leadership, organizational management and business operations, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">accounting and reporting, finance, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">technology and information security, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">mergers and acquisitions, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">legal and regulatory, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">real estate, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">marketing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and public relations</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Michael N. Vittorio - </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Vittorio has been CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of the Corporation and the Bank since 2003</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and is a member of the Loan and Asset Liability Committees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of the Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Prior to his employment by the Company in 2002, Mr. Vittorio was employed at J.P. Morgan Chase as Senior Vice President responsible for managing Chase Insurance Agency&#x2019;s Insurance Brokerage and Advisory Service Business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Previously he served in various capacities at J.P. Morgan Chase including Senior Credit Officer for Small Business Financial Services, Middle Market Regional Manager and Division Executive in the Small Business/Commercial Division.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Vittorio also serves or has served as a director of a variety of not-for-profit entities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Vittorio&#x2019;s experience has provided him with a number of the core competencies identified by the Governance and Nominating Committee, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">which include </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">corporate governance, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">banking,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> strategic planning, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">business leadership, organizational management and business operations, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">mergers and acquisitions, real estate, marketing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and public relations</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="BoardLeadership"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">BOARD LEADERSHIP STRUCTURE</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board has determined that the Chairman of the Board will be an independent director.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board believes that stockholder interests are best served by having a Chairman of the Board who is independent of management and whose exclusive responsibility is the long-term best interest of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Walter C. Teagle III has served as Chairman of the Board since May 2005.&nbsp;&nbsp;As Chairman, Mr. Teagle organizes the work of the Board and ensures that the Board has access to sufficient information to enable it to carry out its</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> functions</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, including monitoring the Corporation&#x2019;s performance and the performance of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the B</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oard and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">management.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The role of the Chairman of the Board includes: (1) presiding over all meetings of the Board and stockholders, including regular executive sessions of the Board in which the C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">E</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">O, a management director, and other members of management do not participate; (2) establishing the annual agenda of the Board and agendas of each meeting in consultation with the CEO; (3) serving as an ex officio member of each board committee and advising wi</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">th respect to the work of each B</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oard committee; (4) coordinating periodic Board reviews of management&#x2019;s strategic plan for the Corporation; and (5) coordinating the Compensation Committee annual performance review of the CEO.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="BoardRoleinRiskOversight"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">BOARD&#x2019;S ROLE IN RISK OVERSIGHT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Risk is an integral part of Board and Board committee discussions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The significant risks facing the Corporation are set forth in an Enterprise Risk Management document.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation&#x2019;s management team, which includes a Chief Risk Officer, is responsible for identifying, assessing and managing risk and the Board is responsible for risk oversight and fulfills this responsibility primarily through its committees.&nbsp;&nbsp;In granting authority to management, approving policies and strategies and receiving management reports, the Board and its committees consider, among other things, the risks that the Corporation faces.&nbsp;&nbsp;For each critical risk, such as credit risk, interest rate risk</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">liquidity risk, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and cybersecurity risk, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Corporation has a formal written policy that is approved by an appropriate Board committee or the full Board.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">As reflected in the Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Board and its committees address succession planning risk both in the ordinary course of business and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> on a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">contingen</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">t basis </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in case of unexpected events.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;The Corporation has comprehensive written succession planning documents that cover the Board and its committees, the CEO and the other members of executive management and from time to time retains consultants with expertise in succession planning matters.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation&#x2019;s succession planning documents are updated no less often than annually and are actively used by the Board and its committees to oversee and ensure a smooth transition should Board members or key members of executive management retire or otherwise leave the employ of the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The following table sets forth the risk oversight responsibilities</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of the Board and Board committees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<div style="width:100%"><table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" align="center" style="border-collapse:collapse;width: 100.00%;line-height:100%;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-left:0pt;">

					<p style="margin:0pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size: 1pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-size:1pt;">&#xFEFF;</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:50.98%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;height:1.00pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;height:1.00pt;overflow:hidden;font-size:0pt;">
						&nbsp;</p>
				</td>

			</tr>

					<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">CEO Succession</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">It is expected that Michael N. Vittorio will retire as President and CEO of the Corporation and the Bank on December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, and in accordance with the terms of his employment agreement, Mr. Vittorio is expected to continue his service as a director until the annual meeting of stockholders following the year ending December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;A process for this planned succession to a new CEO has been underway for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">period of time and is being led by a designated committee of the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The services of a nationally recognized leadership consulting firm have been engaged.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board intends to make a decision and a public announcement as to Mr. Vittorio&#x2019;s successor in a timeframe that will allow for an orderly transition.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:12pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="MeetingsofBOD"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">MEETINGS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">All of the members of the Board of the Corporation also serve on the Board of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board of the Corporation held ten regular </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and three special </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">meetings during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each director attended at least 75% of the aggregate number of Board meetings and meetings of the committees on which such director served.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;The Board meets </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">regularly </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in executive session</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> throughout the year.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="BoardCommitteeMeetings"></a>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">BOARD COMMITTEES AND MEETINGS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board of the Corporation has three standing committees: the Governance and Nominating Committee; the Audit Committee; and the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board of the Bank also has two standing committees: the Loan Committee and the Asset Liability Committee.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Governance and Nominating Committee</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">All the members of the Corporation&#x2019;s Governance and Nominating Committee are independent directors as defined in the Nasdaq Rules.&nbsp;&nbsp;The members of the Governance and Nominating Committee are Paul T. Canarick, Alexander L. Cover, Howard Thomas Hogan, Jr., </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Peter Quick</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Denise Strain, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Milbrey Rennie Taylor and Walter C. Teagle III.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Committee met </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">six </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">times during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s Board has adopted a formal written charter for the Governance and Nominating Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;A current copy of the charter and the Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines are available on the Corporation&#x2019;s website by going to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">www.FNBLI.com</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">placing the cursor over &#x201C;Investor Relations,&#x201D; then clicking on &#x201C;Corporate Governance&#x201D; and then clicking on &#x201C;Board Governance and Nominating Committee Charter&#x201D; or &#x201C;Corporate Governance Guidelines.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Among other things, t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he Governance and Nominating Committee is currently responsible for: </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(1) maintaining the director succession plan; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) identifying individuals qualified to become Board members and recommending to the Board the director nominees for the next annual meeting of stockholders; (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">recommending to the Board written corporate governance guidelines and monitoring compliance with said guidelines; (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) leading the Board in an annual Board self-assessment and reporting to the Board on its own self-assessment and the self-assessments performed by the other Board committees; (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) recommending to the Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> director candidates for each committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; and (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">establishing the director skill sets matrix to evaluate the collective skills of the existing board and to identify skills that may be sought when filling vacancies</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Although the Corporation has a long history of being able to attract and maintain a cohesive Board with the variety of skills necessary to oversee the affairs of the Corporation, the Governance and Nominating Committee will consider director candidates recommended by stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;Submission of candidates may be made in writing at any time.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, to be considered by the Governance and Nominating Committee for nomination at the 20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> annual meeting, such submissions should be made no later than </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">December </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> to the Chair of the Governance and Nominating Committee at the Corporation&#x2019;s address set forth in this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, nominations for the election of directors may be made by any stockholder entitled to vote for the election of directors provided that such nominations are made in accordance with the provisions of the Corporation&#x2019;s bylaws establishing the information and notice requirements for such nominations. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition to interviews, the Governance and Nominating Committee may evaluate potential nominees by reviewing resumes, checking business and/or personal references, and performing background checks as deemed appropriate.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation has not paid a fee to any third party or parties to assist in identifying or evaluating potential nominees.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Except for M</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ives</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">who was </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">appointed </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">by the Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">effective </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">January</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ll of the Class I nominees approved by the Governance and Nominating Committee for inclusion on the Corporation&#x2019;s proxy card for the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to be held April </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> are directors standing for re-election.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;M</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ives </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">introduction</font><font </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">business associate of a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">current </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">non-management </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board member</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Committee</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The members of the Audit Committee are Alexander L. Cover, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">J</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">ohn J. Desmond,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Peter Quick</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Walter C.
