		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s Board has adopted a formal written charter for the Audit Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;A current copy of the charter is available on the Corporation&#x2019;s website by going to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">www.FNBLI.com</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">placing the cursor over &#x201C;Investor Relations,&#x201D; then clicking on &#x201C;Corporate Governance&#x201D; and then clicking on &#x201C;Board Audit Committee Charter.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board has determined that all members of the Audit Committee are independent as independence for audit committee members is defined in SEC Rule 10A-3 and the Nasdaq Rules.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board has also determined that Alexander L. Cover</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">John J. Desmond</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">qualify as</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> an &#x201C;audit committee financial expert&#x201D; as that term is defined in Item 407 of Regulation S-K of the Securities and Exchange Commission.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board has also determined that all members of the Audit Committee have banking or related financial management expertise.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The responsibilities of the Audit Committee are described under the heading &#x201C;Audit Committee Report&#x201D; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> this proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">All the members of the Corporation&#x2019;s Compensation Committee are independent directors as defined in the Nasdaq Rules.&nbsp;&nbsp;The members of the Compensation Committee are </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">John J. Desmond, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Stephen V. Murphy, Milbrey Rennie Taylor, Walter C. Teagle III and Eric J. Tveter.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Committee met </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">five </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">times during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s Board has adopted a formal written charter for the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;A current copy of the charter is available on the Corporation&#x2019;s website by going to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">www.FNBLI.com</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">placing the cursor over &#x201C;Investor Relations,&#x201D; then clicking on &#x201C;Corporate Governance&#x201D; and then clicking on &#x201C;Board Compensation Committee Charter.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The purpose of the Compensation Committee is to assist the Board in fulfilling its oversight responsibilities by reviewing and evaluating the Corporation&#x2019;s compensation practices to ensure that appropriate policies, procedures and systems are in place to identify, measure, and control related risks, including strategic, reputation and operational risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Committee should identify those employees, including but not limited to the CEO and other executive officers, who could potentially expose the Corporation to material amounts of such risk and arrive at compensation for these employees and non-management directors that is appropriate and competitive and does not expose the Corporation to unacceptable risk.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Among other things, t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he Compensation Committee is responsible for: (1) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">implementing and maintaining guiding principles, compensation policies and compensation plans for the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">CEO, other executive officers and non-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">management </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">directors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, all as set forth in the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Proxy Statement for its annual meeting of shareholders,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and reporting and making recommendations to the Board with respect thereto</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> taking into account market competitive data</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (2) recommending to the Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approval of employment agreements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for the CEO and other executive officers;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(3) evaluating the performance of the CEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">against established goals and objectives </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approving for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ratification </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the base salary level for the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> subject to any existing employment agreement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (4) reviewing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the CEO&#x2019;s performance evaluation of the other executive officers of the Corporation and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approving for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> ratification the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">base salary level of each such officer</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> subject to any existing employment agreements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (5) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approving for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ratification </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">cash </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">incentives and bonuses </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to be paid to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the CEO and other executive officers pursuant to the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive compensation plans or otherwise</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">;&nbsp;&nbsp;(6) setting corporate goals</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, objectives and compensation plans </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">used to determine</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> cash incentives and bonuses paid to the CEO and other executive officers and equity compensation awarded to the CEO, other executive officers and non-management directors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &#x2013; the Compensation Committee will periodically engage a compensation consulting firm to assist them in this endeavor</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (7)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approving for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ratification </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">awards of equity compensation to the CEO, other executive officers and non-management directors pursuant to the Corporation&#x2019;s equity compensation plans or otherwise</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (8)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> recommending to the Board compensation proposals such as the compensation to be paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s NEOs, say-on-pay, say-when-on-pay or equity incentive plans to be included in the Corporation&#x2019;s annual proxy statement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; (9) reviewing the overall annual salary budget for the Bank&#x2019;s entire employee population; (10) conducting, or causing to be conducted, at its discretion, a periodic review of the Corporation&#x2019;s pension, 401(k), supplemental executive retirement and health and welfare plans; (11) reviewing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and approving </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">discussion and analysis </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">included in the Corporation&#x2019;s annual proxy statement and preparing or causing to be prepared</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Report</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">be included therein; (12) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">reviewing executive management&#x2019;s determination of compensation of non-executive officers of the Corporation including the total amount of incentive compensation to be paid to such officers; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(13) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">periodically reviewing the incentive compensation plans for senior vice presidents and other employee categories below the level of executive officer; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">considering the results of the most recent non-binding, stockholder advisory vote on executive compensation and, if deemed necessary, recommending to the Board changes in compensation policies, practices and decisions.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">dminist</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> includ</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ing</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> selecting directors and officers to whom awards are to be made and determining the timing, duration, amount, type and terms of each award.&nbsp;&nbsp;Members of the Compensation Committee as well as all other non-employee directors of the Corporation have been eligible for awards of stock-based compensation in the past and it is currently anticipated that they will </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">be eligible for future awards.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In determining an appropriate level of compensation for the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">other executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and the Board</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Compensation Committee periodically engages an independent compensation consulting firm to gather and help analyze the information necessary to make such determinations.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Compensation Committee engaged Pearl Meyer &amp; Partners (&#x201C;PM&amp;P&#x201D;), an independent national compensation consulting firm, to conduct a review of the compensation of the Company&#x2019;s CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">other executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and the B</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oard</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The objective of the review was to provide an assessment of the competitiveness and effectiveness of the Corporation&#x2019;s compensation programs relative to peer banks.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee anticipates engaging a compensation consulting firm in 2019 to perform a similar review.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">In performing their </font><font style="display: inline;">2017 </font><font style="display: inline;">review, PM&amp;P worked with the Compensation Committee to develop a custom </font><font style="display: inline;">peer group.&nbsp;&nbsp;The peer banks </font><font style="display: inline;">were </font><font style="display: inline;">similar in size and scope to the Bank, with </font><font style="display: inline;">total assets </font><font style="display: inline;">averaging </font><font style="display: inline;">approximately $</font><font style="display: year-end 201</font><font style="display: inline;">7</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The peer group consist</font><font style="display: inline;">ed</font><font style="display: Lakeland Bancorp, Inc., </font><font style="display: inline;">Northfield Bancorp, Inc., OceanFirst Financial Corp., </font><font style="display: inline;">Peapack-Gladstone Financial Corporation, Sun Bancorp, Inc., </font><font style="display: inline;">TrustCo Bank Corp NY, </font><font style="display: inline;">Univest Corporation of Pennsylvania and Washington Trust Bancorp, Inc.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">In addition to gathering and analyzing compensation data for the peer group, </font><font style="display: inline;">PM&amp;P also gathered</font><font surveys, including their own survey and surveys performed by</font><font style="display: inline;"> the American Bankers Association</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font compensation</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">annual equity awards</font><font style="display: inline;">, retirement benefits and perquisites</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on their reviews, PM&amp;P provided the Compensation Committee with a comparison of the compensation of the CEO and other executive officers to the market </font><font style="display: inline;">10</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">25</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;">, 50</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">75</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">and 90</font><font style="display: inline;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;"> percentiles</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">PM&amp;P also assessed the elements of Board compensation both individually and in the aggregate, including annual retainers, meeting-based fees and fees for chair roles and special meetings.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the services described above, PM&amp;P</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> was also engaged </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in 2017 </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to perform a review of the structural elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s executive incentive plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee received a letter from PM&amp;P regarding its independence under the six factors to be considered for such purposes under N</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">asdaq</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;R</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ules</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, assessed</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the independence of PM&amp;P pursuant </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to such rules and determined that</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> PM&amp;P is </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">an independent and conflict-free advi</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">sor to the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee considers </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the most recent stockholder say-on-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">pay</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">advisory vote in reviewing the Corporation&#x2019;s executive compensation policies, practices and decisions.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee concluded that no significant revisions were necessary to our executive compensation program as a result of the most recent say</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">on</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">pay</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> advisory vote</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;;font-size: 10pt;font-family:Calibri;text-indent:0pt;margin-left:0pt;padding:0pt 36pt 0pt 0pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee Interlocks and Insider Participation.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;No member of the Compensation Committee: (1) was an officer or employee of the Corporation or the Bank; (2) was formerly an officer of the Corporation or the Bank; or (3) had any relationship requiring disclosure by the Corporation under the SEC&#x2019;s rules governing disclosure of related party transactions.&nbsp; No executive officer of the Corporation served as a director or member of a compensation committee of another entity, one of whose executive officers served as a member of the Corporation&#x2019;s Board or Compensation Committee. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Loan Committee of the Bank </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The members of the Loan Committee are Paul T. Canarick, Howard Thomas Hogan, Jr., Stephen V. Murphy, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Peter Quick, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Denise Strain, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Walter C. Teagle III and Michael N. Vittorio.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Committee met </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">four </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">times during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Loan Committee is responsible for providing oversight with respect to the Bank&#x2019;s lending activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;In this regard, the Committee: (1) oversees credit risk and approves policies that govern lending activities and credit risk management; (2) reviews and ratifies the allowance for loan and lease losses; (3) reviews and approves specific loan transactions where required by policy; and (4) reviews reports from management, internal auditors, the internal loan review function and regulators related to lending activities and credit risk. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Asset Liability Committee of the Bank</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The members of the Asset Liability Committee are Paul T. Canarick, Alexander L. Cover, Stephen V. Murphy, Walter C. Teagle III and Michael N. Vittorio.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Committee met </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">five </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">times during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Asset Liability Committee is responsible for providing oversight with respect to the Bank&#x2019;s achievement of its overall objective of optimizing returns consistent with prudent risk management regarding assets, liabilities, equity and off-balance sheet activities.&nbsp;&nbsp;In this regard, the Committee: (1) oversees investment risk and approves the investment policy limits and operating guidelines set forth in </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Bank&#x2019;s Investment Policy; (2) oversees </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Bank&#x2019;s investment in and management of bank-owned life insurance and approves the pre-purchase, ongoing monitoring and other requirements set forth in the Bank&#x2019;s Bank-Owned Life Insurance Policy; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) oversees interest rate risk and approves the risk limits and operating guidelines set forth in the Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x2019;s Interest Rate Risk Policy; (4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) oversees liquidity risk and approves the risk limits and operating guidelines set forth in the Bank&#x2019;s Liquidity Policy and Liquidity Contingency Plan; and (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">) oversees management&#x2019;s use</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of embedded and stand-alone derivative instruments for purposes</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of managing interest rate risk and approves the hedging policy </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">appendix </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of the Bank&#x2019;s interest rate risk policy.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="BoardMemberAttendance"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">BOARD MEMBER ATTENDANCE AT ANNUAL MEETINGS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board strongly encourages each of its members to attend the Annual Meeting of Stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;In this regard, the Board sets the date for the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to coincide with its April Board meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;All directors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">attended the prior year&#x2019;s Annual Meeting of Stockholders which was h</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eld on April </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="SecurityHolderCommunications"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">SECURITY</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">HOLDER COMMUNICATIONS TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s Board does not hav</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">e a formal process for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">security holders</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> to send communications to the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board believes that a formal process is unnecessary because the Corporation is relatively small and both the Chairman of the Board and the CEO, who is also a director, are easily accessible by telephone and mail.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

				<td valign="top" style="border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;width:45.84%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Loan Committee</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="top" style="border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;width:24.16%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">$11,000</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="top" style="border-left:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;width:30.00%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;background-color: #CCEEFF;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">$4,000</font></p>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">There are no per meeting fees for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">standing </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">committee meetings</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Loan Committee members are paid $500 for each Management Loan Committee meeting attended</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ad-Hoc Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">chairs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">are paid </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">fees ranging from $500 to $1,000 and Ad-Hoc Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">members </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">are paid </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">fees ranging from $500 to $750 </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">meeting attended</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Chairman does not receive per meeting fees or committee retainers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO does not receive retainers or per meeting fees for Board or Board committee service. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Stock-based Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s 2014 Equity Incentive Plan </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(&#x201C;2014 Plan&#x201D;) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">allows for the granting of equity awards to non-employee directors of the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity compensation for directors consists of restricted stock units (&#x201C;RSUs&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">grant date fair </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">value </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of RSUs granted to the Chairman and each non-employee director </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">in 2019 based on 2018 service was $70,000 and $35,000, respectively</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">RSUs granted to non-employee directors </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">i</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">n 2016</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> through </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">are time-based RSUs that vest ratably and convert into shares of Common Stock over a three-year time period.&nbsp;&nbsp;The RSUs granted in January 2016 also receive</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> annual cash dividend</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> equivalent</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s at the same rate as the dividends declared by the Board on the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ommon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">tock.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">All outstanding</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> granted to directors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> immediately vest upon a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">n involuntary termination following a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">change in control, total and permanent disability</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or death</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Retirement Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">On June 18, 1991, the Board of the Bank adopted The First National Bank of Long Island Retirement Plan for Directors ("Retirement Plan").&nbsp;&nbsp;Effective December 31, 2000, benefits earned </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to date</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> under the Retirement Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> were frozen and the ability of directors to earn additional benefits was discontinued.&nbsp;&nbsp;Upon retirement after attaining the age of sixty (60), each of the current directors who was a director prior to 2001 will receive a credit ("Credit Percentage") of ten percent (10%) multiplied by the number of years of service on the Board through December 31, 2000, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">not to exceed</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> one hundred percent (100%).&nbsp;&nbsp;The annual benefit ("Annual Benefit") </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">payable </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">under the Retirement Plan is equal to the monthly Board of Directors&#x2019; attendance fee in effect as of December 31, 2000</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, which was</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> $1,000, multiplied by twelve (12) and then multiplied by the Credit Percentage.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Annual Benefit is payable in quarterly installments for a period of seven (7) years from the date of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">retirement (</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">"Payment Period").&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of the death of a director or a retired director, the surviving spouse of such director is entitled to receive an annual payment equal to seventy-five percent (75%) of the Annual Benefit, calculated as set forth above, and payable over the remainder of the applicable Payment Period.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Messrs. Canarick, Hogan and Teagle are the only directors participating in the Retirement Plan.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The following table sets forth information concerning the compensation of directors for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>

				<td valign="top" style="border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;width:11.38%;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">59</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="top" style="border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;width:44.40%;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<a name="_Hlk535848118"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Executive Vice President of the Corporation and the Bank; Senior Credit Officer of the Bank</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="top" style="border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-right:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;width:19.18%;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">2006</font></p>
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">12</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Mr. Hilton joined the Bank in June 2017 as Senior Vice President and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Commercial Banking Division Executive.&nbsp;&nbsp;On January 1, 2018, Mr. Hilton was promoted to Executive Vice President of the Corporation and the Bank.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Prior to joining the Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Suffolk County National Bank and its holding company, Suffolk Bancorp, until its acquisition by People&#x2019;s United Bank in April 2017.&nbsp; Mr. Hilton joined People&#x2019;s United Bank and served as Senior Credit Officer until May 2017.&nbsp; Prior to his employment at Suffolk County National Bank, Mr. Hilton served as Executive Vice President &amp; Chief Credit Officer of Empire National Bank and Vice President of its holding company, Empire Bancorp.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Ms. Stefanucci joined the Bank in 2006 and for the past six years was Senior Vice President, Credit Risk and Administration Officer.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms. Stefanucci was promoted to Executive Vice President of the Corporation and the Bank effective December 1, 2018 and is the Bank&#x2019;s Senior Credit Officer.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Proposal2ApproveCompensationPaidtoNEOs"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROPOSAL 2</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">NON-BINDING, ADVISORY VOTE TO APPROVE THE COMPENSATION PAID TO THE </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">CORPORATION&#x2019;S NAMED EXECUTIVE OFFICERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The compensation paid to our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> is disclosed in this proxy statement in the sections entitled &#x201C;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation of Executive Officers,&#x201D; &#x201C;Compensation Pursu</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ant to Plans&#x201D; and &#x201C;Employment Agreements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&#x201D;&nbsp;&nbsp;We believe that our compensation policies, practices and decisions are focused on pay-for-performance principles and are strongly aligned with the long-term best interests of our stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation of our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> is designed to enable us to attract and retain talented and experienced senior executives to lead the Corporation successfully in a competitive environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;Stockholders are being asked to cast a non-binding, advisory vote on the following resolution:</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">RESOLVED, that the compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> as disclosed in its proxy statement for the April </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting of Stockholders pursuant to Item 402 of Regulation S-K, including the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, compensation tables and narrative discussion, is hereby APPROVED. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of shares represented in person or by proxy and voting on this item will be required for approval.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Your vote on this Proposal 2 is advisory, and therefore not binding on the Corporation, the Compensation Committee or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;The vote will not be construed to overrule any decision by the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or the Board; to create or imply any change to the fiduciary duties of the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or the Board; or to create or imply any additional fiduciary duties for the Corporation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or the Board.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, our Board and our Compensation Committee value the opinions of our stockholders and to the extent there is a significant vote against the compensation paid to our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> as disclosed in this proxy statement, we will consider our stockholders&#x2019; concerns and the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Board and the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Compensation Committee will evaluate whether any actions are necessary to address those concerns.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR the proposal to approve the</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">compensation paid to the Corporation&#x2019;s named executive officers.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationCommitteeReport"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">COMPENSATION COMMITTEE REPORT</font>
		</p>

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">We have reviewed and discussed with management the Compensation Discussion and Analysis included herein and provided pursuant to Item 402(b) of Regulation S-K.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Based on this review and discussion, we recommended to the Board that the Compensation Discussion and Analysis be included in this proxy statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee:</font>

		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationDiscussionandAnalysis"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">COMPENSATION DISCUSSION AND ANALYSIS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The following is a discussion of the compensation awarded to, earned by or paid to the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The discussion explains all the material elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s compensation of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;It should be read in conjunction with the other executive compensation disclosures that appear elsewhere in this proxy statement.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Guiding Principles</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">In designing and maintaining a compensation program for the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> other executive officers and employees,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> the Compensation Committee adheres to the following guiding principles:</font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">13</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>
