			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (1)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The compensation program should be principles-based, employ best practices in executive compensation and consider all relevant regulatory guidance regarding sound incentive compensation policies.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (2)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The compensation program should be designed and supervised by the Compensation Committee with, as needed, the assistance of independent compensation consultants, legal counsel and other advisors who have significant experience in risk management, compensation practices and legal matters in the financial services industry.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (3)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee should consist entirely of independent directors and operate under a charter adopted by the Board that clearly defines its duties and responsibilities.&nbsp;&nbsp;Significant approvals by the Compensation Committee regarding the provisions of the executive compensation program and awards thereunder should be ratified by the full Board.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (4)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">A significant portion of executive compensation awarded under the program should be directly tied to corporate performance and thereby closely aligned with the interests of stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;The corporate performance levels necessary to earn threshold, target and maximum cash incentive and equity awards should be determined by the Compensation Committee and should not encourage inappropriate risks that could lead to material financial loss to the Bank.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (5)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The compensation program should enable the Corporation to attract and retain highly skilled professionals in each necessary discipline (i.e., executive, financial, lending, operations, risk management).</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (6)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Compensation paid should be appropriately balanced between short and long-term components.&nbsp;&nbsp;The short-term components should</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> primarily</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> consist of base salary and cash incentive compensation and the long-term components should be equity awards that vest over time as well as retirement benefits.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (7)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The competitiveness of total direct compensation, which consists of base salary, cash incentive and equity awards, should be tested regularly by a comparison to: (1) a group of peer banks selected by the Compensation Committee that are similar in size and scope to the Corporation; and (2) amounts published in compensation surveys for the banking industry conducted by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (8)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The compensation program should achieve internal equity among the Corporation&#x2019;s executive officers.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (9)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Retirement benefits should be market competitive and evaluated based on the percentage of the executive&#x2019;s income replaced in retirement.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (10)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Payments upon a change in control or termination should be market competitive, reasona</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ble in amount and designed to en</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">sure that the executive officers of the Bank are not significantly harmed nor unduly enriched and are therefore objective with respect to the consummation of a transaction, such as a sale or merger of the Bank, that may be in the best interests of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders. </font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (11)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee should identify those employees, whether they </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">are</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> executive officers or otherwise, who could potentially expose the Corporation to material amounts of risk.&nbsp;&nbsp;The compensation of such employees should be designed to discourage imprudent risk taking and contain maximum incentive amounts that do not represent windfalls.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (12)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Clawbacks should be utilized within the compensation program </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">in accordance with our clawback policy and applicable law</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (13)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Retention of vested or exercised equity awards should be required </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">until </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">stock ownership guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> are met</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (14)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Employees, whether they are</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> executive officers or otherwise, should be prohibited from hedging the value of equity compensation that vests over time.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (15)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Performance </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">goals should be established by the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and ratified by the full Board.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 21.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (16)</font>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:15pt;"><p style="width:15pt;width:15pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Achievement of performance goals should be certified by the Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">prior to the payment of awards.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Objectives of the Executive Compensation Program</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Corporation&#x2019;s executive compensation program is designed to enable the Corporation to attract and retain talent</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ed executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> necessary to safely and successfully operate and grow the Bank.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;The executive compensation program promotes sound risk management and long-term value creation for our stockholders.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">What the Executive Compensation Program is Designed to Reward</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Certain elements of the executive compensation program are intended to reward current performance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">By offering long-term equity compensation, the executive compensation program is </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">also </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">designed to reward executive officers who help maximize long-term financial performance and earnings growth of the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Elements of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The executive compensation program consists of four basic components: (1) base salary; (2) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">cash incentive compensation; (3) equity awards; and (4) other noncash compensation, consisting primarily of retirement benefits</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and reasonable perquisites</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">14</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Why We Choose To Pay Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Base Salary.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;The Compensation Committee believes that base salary for a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">n</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">should compensate the officer for the skills and effort required to perform the officer&#x2019;s day-to-day responsibilities, taking into account the size and complexity of the Compa</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ny.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Cash Incentive</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;"> Compensation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;The Compensation Committee has included annual cash incentive compensation in the executive compensation program as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance through, among other things, the achievement of annual corporate goals set forth in the Corporation&#x2019;s strategic plan.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Our Compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Committee recom</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">mended, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Board </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">adopted and the stockholders approved</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the 2016 Cash Incentive Plan, which provides the opportunity for a cash incentive payment based upon the achievement of corporate and individual goals. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-indent:18pt;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;font-size:10pt;">Equity Awards</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee uses equity awards granted under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan as a means to incent executive officers to optimize corporate performance over a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">n extended </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">time-period.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity awards, together with retirement benefits, are the longer-term components of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> executive</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> compensation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:18pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;">Other Noncash Compensation.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;Other noncash compensation consists of: (1) retirement benefits paid under the Bank&#x2019;s defined benefit pension plan</font><font style="display: inline;"> (&#x201C;Pension Plan&#x201D;), 401(k) P</font><font style="display: inline;">lan and Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan (&#x201C;SERP&#x201D;); and (2) noncash fringe benefits not available to the general employee population of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;Noncash fringe benefits, other than those available to the general employee population at the Bank, include the personal use of business automobiles and </font><font style="display: inline;">a &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">country club</font><font style="display: inline;"> membership for the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Retirement benefits provided by the Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;">P</font><font style="display: inline;">ension</font><font style="display: inline;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;">s are </font><font style="display: inline;">intended</font><font style="display: inline;"> to encourage </font><font style="display: inline;">the</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;"> to maintain their employment with the Corporation and maximize long-term corporate performance.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP</font><font style="display: inline;">, of which </font><font style="display: inline;">the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;"> is</font><font style="display: inline;"> the only participant</font><font style="display: inline;">,</font><font style="display: inline;"> provides</font><font style="display: inline;"> the additional pension and 401(k) benefits that </font><font style="display: inline;">t</font><font style="display: inline;">he </font><font style="display: inline;">CEO </font><font style="display: inline;">would receive in the absence of Internal Revenue Code provisions which limit the amount of compensation that can be considered in determining retirement benefits to be paid under the Bank&#x2019;s tax-qualified retirement plans.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">The SERP is explained in the &#x201C;PENSION BENEFIT</font><font style="display: inline;">S</font><font style="display: inline;">&#x201D; section of this proxy statement.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">A country club membership is provided to the CEO to aid him in developing and retaining business.&nbsp;&nbsp;Business automobiles are provided to all of the Bank&#x2019;s executive officers as a competitive perquisite and as an alternative to reimbursing such officers for mileage driven on account of business conducted on behalf of the Corporation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">How We Determine The Amount To Pay For Each Element of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The total compensation paid by the Corporation to each of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> is based on a variety of factors including: (1) the Company&#x2019;s recent and expected future overall financial performance; (2) current economic conditions and the effect thereof on the Company&#x2019;s performance and that of its peers; (3) the executive officer&#x2019;s experience and tenure in his or her current po</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">sition, years of service to</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Bank, scope of responsibilities, leadership ability, compensation relative to the Company&#x2019;s other executive officers, recent and expected future performance, and contributions to corporate performance; (4) a comparison of total compensation and each element of compensation paid to the executive to compensation amounts paid by peer banks to executives with similar roles and compensation amounts set forth in published industry surveys for executives with similar roles; and (5) the most recent stockholder advisory vote on executive compensation.&nbsp;&nbsp;As previously discussed, comparative compensation studies are performed and updated on a periodic basis by an independent compensation consulting firm engaged by and working under the direction of the Compensation Committee.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Base salary for the CEO is reviewed by the Compensation Committee on an annual basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">also performs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> an annual review of the base salary recommendations made by the CEO for the Company&#x2019;s other </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each executive officer does not necessarily receive an increase in base salary each year.&nbsp;&nbsp;In reviewing each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x2019;s base salary, the Compensation Committee considers the amounts paid by peer banks</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> amounts set forth in compensation surveys performed by nationally recognized independent compensation consulting firms</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Corporation&#x2019;s overall budget for base salary increases.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Regular annual </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">salary increases for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for the NEOs ranged from </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">% to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">%</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and averaged </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">12</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">%</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">For the Corporation&#x2019;s CEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and CFO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">annual</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">cash incentive compensation has been</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> based on corporate performance measured by net income, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">return on assets (&#x201C;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ROA</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x201D;)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">bank safety</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and Compensation Committee discretion</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ash incentive compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for the other NEOs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">has been</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> based on a combination of corporate and personal performance with </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">weights of 80% and 20%, respectively, for Mr. Becker, 70% and 30%, respectively, for Mr. Hilton and 50% </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">for Mr. Daley.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporate </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">performance for the other NEOs is measured by net income, ROA, bank safety and Compensation Committee discretion, and p</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ersonal performance is measured by the achievement of goals, monetary and nonmonetary, assigned</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> to the NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Compensation Committee disc</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">retion is </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">based on, among other things, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a qualitative assessment of corporate performance in light of current conditions. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The following table sets forth the range of annual cash incentive compensation for 201</font><font style="display: inline;">8</font><font style="display: inline;"> under the 201</font><font style="display: inline;">6</font><font style="display: inline;"> Cash Incentive Plan assuming that the Corporation achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance</font><font style="display: inline;"> and, where applicable, the NEO achieved threshold, target and maximum levels of performance with respect to personal goals</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">Each NEO</font><font style="display: inline;">&#x2019;</font><font style="display: inline;">s cash incentive target for 201</font><font style="display: inline;">8</font><font style="display: inline;"> was a percentage of base salary as </font><font style="display: inline;">determined by the Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">Achievement of corporate</font><font style="display: inline;"> and</font><font style="display: inline;">,</font><font style="display: inline;"> where applicable</font><font style="display: inline;">,</font><font style="display: inline;"> personal </font><font style="display: inline;">performance levels greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level results in</font><font style="display: inline;"> a cash incentive payment that is proportionately greater than the threshold level of incentive but less than the maximum level of incentive.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">15</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;;font-size: 11pt"><font style="display: inline;"></font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>

					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 9pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;">NEO</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:24.68%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #auto;height:15.05pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 9pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;">Threshold ($)</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:24.68%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #auto;height:15.05pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 9pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;">Target ($)</font></p>
				</td>
				<td valign="bottom" style="width:24.68%;border-top:1pt solid #000000 ;border-left:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt solid #000000 ;border-right:1pt solid #000000 ;background-color: #auto;height:15.05pt;padding:0pt 6.5pt">
					<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 9pt">
						<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:9pt;">Maximum ($)</font></p>
				</td>
			</tr>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Equity ince</font><font style="display: inline;">ntive compensation </font><font style="display: inline;">for </font><font style="display: inline;">the NEOs </font><font style="display: inline;">before 2019 </font><font style="display: inline;">primarily consisted of </font><font style="display: inline;">performance-based </font><font style="display: inline;">RSUs that were </font><font style="display: inline;">awarded </font><font style="display: inline;">based on corporate performance measured by the same metrics used for cash incentive compensation</font><font style="display: inline;">. &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">Equity awards before 2019 also </font><font style="display: inline;">occasionally included smaller amounts of </font><font style="display: inline;">time-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">that </font><font style="display: inline;">were based on the discretion of the Compensation Committee after considering, among other things, the strength and consistency of the Corporation&#x2019;s performance over an extended period of time.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">Performance-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">award</font><font style="display: inline;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;"> before 2018 </font><font style="display: inline;">vest</font><font style="display: inline;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;"> and convert</font><font style="display: inline;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;"> into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for the final year of the three calendar year performance period beginning with the year in which the RSUs were awarded.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;Performance-based RSUs awarded </font><font style="display: inline;">in 2018 </font><font style="display: inline;">included two-thirds (&#x2154;) </font><font style="display: inline;">that were </font><font style="display: inline;">performance-based and one-third (&#x2153;) </font><font style="display: inline;">that were </font><font style="display: inline;">time-based.</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">One-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for 2018, one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for 2019 and the final one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts three years from the date of grant.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Equity incentive compensation </font><font style="display: inline;">for </font><font style="display: inline;">the NEOs in </font><font style="display: inline;">2019 </font><font style="display: inline;">consisted of RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">that </font><font style="display: inline;">were </font><font style="display: inline;">awarded </font><font style="display: inline;">based on a fixed percentage of salary as determined by the Compensation Committee.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;These awards includ</font><font style="display: inline;">e</font><font style="display: inline;"> two-thirds (&#x2154;) that </font><font style="display: inline;">are </font><font style="display: inline;">performance-based and one-third (&#x2153;) that </font><font style="display: inline;">are </font><font style="display: inline;">time-based.&nbsp;&nbsp;One-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts into shares of Common Stock based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for 2019, one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts based on the satisfaction of net income and ROA performance metrics for 2020 and the final one-third (&#x2153;) vests and converts three years from the date of grant.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;Multi-year performance periods for the performance-based RSUs encourage long-term strategic focus.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">P</font><font style="display: inline;">erformance-based RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">granted in </font><font style="display: inline;">2017</font><font style="display: inline;">,</font><font style="display: inline;"> 2018</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">and 2019 </font><font style="display: inline;">have upside conversion potential in that a</font><font style="display: inline;"> maximum level of performance will result in </font><font style="display: inline;">the distribution of more than one share of Common Stock for </font><font style="display: inline;">one RSU</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;For the 2017 grant, </font><font style="display: inline;">a maximum level of performance </font><font style="display: inline;">will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for </font><font style="display: inline;">one-and-one-</font><font style="display: inline;">quarter (</font><font style="display: inline;">1</font><font style="display: inline;">&#xBC;) </font><font style="display: inline;">shares of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance greater than the t</font><font style="display: inline;">hreshold</font><font style="display: inline;"> level but less than the maximum level will result in a conversion ratio proportionately greater than one RSU for </font><font style="display: inline;">one-half </font><font style="display: inline;">(&#xBD;) </font><font style="display: inline;">share of Common Stock but less than one RSU for</font><font style="display: inline;"> one-and-one-</font><font style="display: inline;">quarter </font><font style="display: inline;">(</font><font style="display: inline;">1</font><font style="display: inline;">&#xBC;) </font><font style="display: inline;">shares of Common Stock.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">For the 2018 and 2019 grants, a maximum level of performance will result in a conversion ratio of one RSU for one-and-one-</font><font style="display: inline;">half</font><font style="display: inline;"> (1</font><font style="display: inline;">&#xBD;</font><font style="display: inline;">) shares of Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Performance greater than the threshold level but less than the maximum level will result in a conversion ratio proportionately greater than one RSU for one-half (&#xBD;) share of Common Stock but less than one RSU for one-and-one-</font><font style="display: inline;">half</font><font style="display: inline;"> (1</font><font style="display: inline;">&#xBD;</font><font style="display: inline;">) shares of Common Stock.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">The </font><font style="display: inline;">maximum level of performance</font><font style="display: inline;"> for RSUs granted before 2018</font><font style="display: inline;"> has been </font><font style="display: inline;">125% of the target level, whereas the th</font><font style="display: inline;">reshold level of performance has been </font><font style="display: inline;">75% of the target level.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;For the RSUs granted in </font><font style="display: inline;">2018</font><font style="display: inline;"> and 2019</font><font style="display: inline;">, the maximum level of performance is 115% of the target level, whereas the threshold level of performance is 80% of the target level. </font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">For the RSUs granted </font><font style="display: inline;">in </font><font style="display: inline;">201</font><font style="display: inline;">7</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">exceeding the target level of performance by 25% results in vesting 25% more than the target level of shares, </font><font style="display: inline;">while </font><font style="display: inline;">falling 25% short of the target level of performance results in vesting 50% less than the target level of shares.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;For the RSUs granted in 2018</font><font style="display: inline;"> and 2019</font><font style="display: inline;">, exceeding the target level of performance by 15% results in vesting 50% more than the target level of shares, while </font><font style="display: inline;">falling 20</font><font style="display: inline;">% short of the target level of performance results in vesting 50% less than the target level of shares. </font><font style="display: inline;"> Falling short by more than 25%</font><font style="display: inline;"> for the </font><font style="display: inline;">2017 </font><font style="display: inline;">RSU grant and 20% for the 2018 </font><font style="display: inline;">and 2019 </font><font style="display: inline;">grant</font><font style="display: inline;">s</font><font style="display: inline;"> results in expiration of the RSUs without any vesting of the target le</font><font style="display: inline;">vel of shares.&nbsp;&nbsp;The </font><font style="display: inline;">punitive impact of falling short of the target level of performance and the upside potential for exceeding the target level of performance is designed to encourage senior management to outperform.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;In setting </font><font style="display: inline;">the current </font><font style="display: inline;">threshold, target and maximum level</font><font style="display: inline;">s of performance and related</font><font style="display: inline;"> payouts, the Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;">utilized the study performed by PM&amp;P of the structural elements of the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive compensation plan and </font><font style="display: inline;">considered, among other things, performance and payout levels for the Corporation&#x2019;s peer banks.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Over the last three years, cash incentive compensation for the NEOs as a group has averaged approximately one</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">third (</font><font style="display: inline;">&#x2153;</font><font style="display: inline;">) of total incentive compensation, while equity incentive compensation has averaged approximately two</font><font style="display: inline;">-</font><font style="display: inline;">thirds </font><font style="display: inline;">(&#x2154;) </font><font style="display: inline;">of total incentive compensation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">By their terms, a</font><font style="display: inline;">ll</font><font style="display: inline;"> outstanding</font><font style="display: inline;"> performance-based</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">RSUs held by NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disability, as defined, or death</font><font style="display: inline;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;F</font><font style="display: inline;">or </font><font style="display: inline;">performance-based </font><font style="display: inline;">RSUs granted in 2018</font><font style="display: inline;"> and 2019</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">upon retirement vesting will occur </font><font style="display: inline;">only after the </font><font style="display: inline;">completion of the applicable performance period and attainment of the relevant performance criteria.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">For</font><font style="display: inline;"> performance-based</font><font style="display: inline;"> RSUs granted before 2018</font><font style="display: inline;"> to NEOs, other than the </font><font style="display: inline;">Chief Financial Officer (&#x201C;</font><font style="display: inline;">CFO</font><font style="display: inline;">&#x201D;)</font><font style="display: inline;">, i</font><font style="display: inline;">n the event of retirement, and in </font><font style="display: inline;">order to qualify as tax-deductible</font><font style="display: inline;"> performance-b</font><font style="display: inline;">ased compensation under the pre-</font><font style="display: inline;">2018 provisions of Section 162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code</font><font style="display: inline;">, &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">vesting </font><font style="display: inline;">can only occur upon completion of the related performance period and attainment of the relevant performance criteria.&nbsp;&nbsp;The</font><font style="display: inline;"> performance-based</font><font style="display: inline;"> RSUs </font><font style="display: inline;">granted to </font><font style="display: inline;">the CFO </font><font style="display: inline;">before </font><font style="display: inline;">2018 </font><font style="display: inline;">immediately vest in the event of retirement because the CFO is exempt from the pre-2018 provisions of Section 162(m).&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;">A</font><font style="display: inline;">ll outstanding time-based RSUs granted to </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">16</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">NEOs immediately vest in the event of an involuntary termination following a change in control, total and permanent disab</font><font style="display: inline;">ility, as defined, or death, and</font><font style="display: inline;">, unlike</font><font style="display: inline;"> many of</font><font style="display: inline;"> the performance-based RSUs, also immediately vest in the event of retirement.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp;For a further discussion of the tax-deductibility of executive compensation, see</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">the </font><font style="display: inline;">Tax Deductibi</font><font style="display: inline;">lity of Executive Compensation section of this proxy statement.</font>
		</p>

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The value of a RSU realized at vesting can be more or less than its grant date fair value if the Common Stock price at the date of vesting is more or less than its fair market value on the date of grant</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the aggregate conversion ratio described above is</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> more or</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> less than one RSU for one share of Common Stock.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
