		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">In the future the Compensation Committee may use different metrics to measure corporate performance such as earnings per share, return on average stockholders&#x2019; equity or the efficiency ratio</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">, or may change the weights applied to each metric</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee believes that </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">total </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">t</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">arget</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> remuneration</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> for executive officers should be market competitive</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">, benchmarked to the 50</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> percentile of </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">the Bank&#x2019;s peer group</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> and take into consideration individual and corporate performance and tenure</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">In performing their</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> 2017</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> review of executive compensation, PM&amp;P </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">compiled</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> compensation data from the </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">proxy statements of the </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Corporation&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">custom </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">peer group and </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">from</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> published industry surveys </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">and, based on this data, calculated </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">percentile amounts against which total compensation for the </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">Company</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">&#x2019;s </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">could be compared.&nbsp;&nbsp;The PM&amp;P study showed that total </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">target </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">compensation for all </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">NEOs ranged from the 19</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> to</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> the 54</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">th</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;"> percentile</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">.</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Termination and Change in Control Payments</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Each of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> has an employment agreement wi</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">th the Corporation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">that provides for severance compensation in the event</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> that the executive is terminated by the Board without cause or terminates his employment for Good Reason, as defined, whether or not such termination occurs in connection with a change in control (see Employment Agreements section of this proxy statement).&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">These provisions are </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">designed to insure, among other things, that the NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> are not significantly harmed or unduly enriched and are therefore objective with respect to the consummation of a transaction, such as a sale or merger of the Bank that may be in the best interests of the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders.&nbsp;&nbsp;In determining the severance arrangement for the CEO and each of th</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">e other NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, the Compensation Committee considered the severance arrangements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> offered b</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">y peer banks to their </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">17</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Impact of Accounting and Tax Treatment of Certain Elements of Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">has </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">grant</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ed</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">non-qualified stock options (&#x201C;NQSOs&#x201D;) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and RSUs as equity compensation.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NQSOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> are advantageous from the Corporation&#x2019;s standpoint because the Corporation records a book tax benefit for the compensation cost recognized for financial statement reporting purposes under FASB ASC Topic 718 and receives a tax benefit upon the exercise of in-the-money </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NQSOs and the vesting of RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Tax Deductibility of Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Internal Revenue Code Section 162(m)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">limits the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">tax </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">deducti</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">bility of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">compensation paid to any covered employee to $1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> million</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> per year.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Tax Cuts and Jobs Act </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(the &#x201C;Act&#x201D;) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">was signed into law on December 22, 2017</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and amends Section 162(m) to treat all NEOs as covered employees (previously the CFO was</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> not</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> a covered employee) and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eliminate the exclusion of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">qualified </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">performance-based compensation in determining compensation subject to the $1 million limitation.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition, the Act provides &#x201C;grandfathered&#x201D; treatment for qualified performance-based compensation in excess of $1 million that meets the requirements of Section 162(m), is payable pursuant to a written binding contract in effect as of November 2, 2017 and is not modified in any material respect.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">M</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ost of the compensation paid to the NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> as a group</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">through year-end 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> wa</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s deductible under </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the applicable provisions of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Section 162(m)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">A number of requirements must be met for particular compensation to qualify for tax deductibility, so there can be no assurance that incentive compensation paid to the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">NEOs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">will be fully deductible in all circumstances.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">will consider the impact of the Act on the design of our executive compensation programs going forward.&nbsp;&nbsp;While the Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">does not have a formal policy with respect to the payment of compensation in excess of the deduction limit under Code Section 162(m)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he Compensation Committee&#x2019;s practice is to structure compensation programs offered to the NEOs with a view towards maximizing tax deductibility of amounts paid.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, in structuring compensation programs, the Compensation Committee considers a variety of factors, including the Corporation&#x2019;s tax position, the materiality of the payments and tax deductions involved and the need for flexibility to address unforeseen circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;After considering these factors, the Compensation Committee may decide to authorize payments, all or part of which may be nondeductible for federal</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> income</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> tax purposes.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Role of Executive Officers In Determining Executive Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Committee approves the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">proposed compensation of executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> after considering, among other things, executive compensation studies</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> periodically </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">performed by</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> independent compensation consult</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ing firms</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;From time to time, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">E</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">O</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and CFO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">have served as a resource to the Compensation Committee in gathering the information necessary to make such compensation determinations.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">However, these officers do not have a policy-making role with respect to determining the amount or form of executive compensation and do not participate in Compensation Committee deliberations regarding their own compensation.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Compensation Policies and Practices As They Relate To Risk Management</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation has a written incentive-based compensation policy that sets forth governance roles for the Compensation Committee, senior management and the Corporation&#x2019;s internal auditors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The policy is reviewed annually by the Compensation Committee, modified if deemed appropriate and approved.&nbsp;&nbsp;T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">he purpose of the policy is to e</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">nsure that the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive-based compensation arrangements, or any feature of any such arrangement, do not encourage executive officers or employees to: (1) expose the Corporation to inappropriate risks by providing such persons with excessive compensation, fees or benefits; or (2) take inappropriate risks that could lead to material financial loss to the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;Pursuant to this policy, the Corporation&#x2019;s incentive-based compensation arrangements are required to: (1) balance risk and financial rewards, through such things as risk adjustments of awards, deferral of payments, longer performance periods and/or reduced sensitivity to short-term performance; (2) be compatible with effective internal controls and risk management; and (3) be supported by strong corporate governance, including active and effective oversight by the Compensation Committee.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Compensation Committee has determined that the Company&#x2019;s compensation policies and practices for its employees, including non-executive officers, are not reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on the Company.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Stock Ownership Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> and Equity Award Retention Policy</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">As a condition to receiving equity awarded under the Corporation&#x2019;s equity incentive plan each director and executive officer shall enter into an agreement</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">with the Company providing that any stock acquired from the exercise of stock options or the vesting of equity awards, net of the disposition of shares for tax withholding requirements, must be held until stock ownership requirements are met.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Each director of the Corporation is required to have beneficial ownership of shares of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ommon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">tock of the Corporation with a current market value equal to three (3) times cash retainers, which includes Committee retainers and per meeting fees.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO of the Corporation is required to have beneficial ownership of shares of common stock of the Corporation with a current market value equal to three (3) times his </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or her </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">current base salary.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each other executive officer of the Corporation is required t</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">o have beneficial ownership of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">shares of common stock of the Corporation with </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a current market value equal to one (1) times his or her current base salary.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">All ownership requirements need to be met as follows: </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1) within five years of becoming a director or executive officer; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2) within five years of an increase in ownership requirements for the incremental increase only; or </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">(</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">3) within three years of falling out of compliance with these requirements due to compensation increases or fluctuations in market value.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">18</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Clawback Policy</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Corporation has </font><font style="display: inline;">a clawback policy to </font><font style="display: inline;">enable the Company to </font><font style="display: inline;">recover </font><font style="display: inline;">any bonus or incentive compensation awarded or paid </font><font style="display: inline;">to the Company&#x2019;s executive officers if</font><font style="display: inline;">:</font><font style="display: inline;"> (1) the payments or awards were based on materially inaccurate financial statements or any other materially inaccurate performance metric, and (2) the amount of the incentive compensation, as calculated under restated financial results, is less than the amount actually paid or awarded under the original financial results.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Anti-Hedging Policy</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Directors, NEOs, other officers and employees are prohibited from hedging the Corporation&#x2019;s securities with the use of financial instruments (including prepaid variable forward contracts, equity swaps, calls, puts</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> collars, and exchange funds) that offset a decre</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ase in the market value of the C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ompany&#x2019;s equity securities and any other transaction with comparable economic consequences.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Shareholder Advisory Vote on Compensation</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">considers </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the results of the annual say</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">on</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">pay stockholder advisory vote on the compensation paid to NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;To the extent there is a significant vote against the compensation paid to our NEOs, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">the Compensation Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">will consider our stockholders&#x2019; concerns and evaluate whether any actions are necessary to addr</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ess tho</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">se concerns.&nbsp;&nbsp;At the 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting of Stockholders, there was substantial support for the say</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">on</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">-</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">pay proposal</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> with approximately 97% of the votes cast on the proposal v</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">oting in support of the compensation outlined in last year&#x2019;s proxy statement.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">After a comprehensive market review and in light of strong stockholder support, the Compensation Committee concluded that no significant revisions were necessary to our executive compensation program.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationofExecutiveOfficers"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">COMPENSATION OF EXECUTIVE OFFICERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The following table sets forth information with respect to the aggregate compensation paid, earned or awarded for the years ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> to the CEO, CFO and each of the additional three most highly compensated executive officers of the Bank.&nbsp;&nbsp;All compensation information is provided pursuant to the SEC</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">executive compensation disclosure rules for proxy statements.&nbsp;&nbsp;All of the listed officers are also officers of the Corporation but received salaries only from the Bank. </font>

			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The amounts shown for each year represent RSU grants for that year but granted subsequent to the close of the year.&nbsp;&nbsp;T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">he aggregate grant date fair values </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">are </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">computed in accordance with FASB ASC Topic 718.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The values shown for 2016 include time-based RSU</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">that </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">were a discretionary grant by the Compensation Committee after considering, among other things, the Corporation&#x2019;s strong financial performance for 2016 and its consistent earnings growth ov</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">er an extended period of time.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The amounts shown for each year represent cash incentive compensation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">earned </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">based on performance for that year but paid subsequent to the close of the year.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;">
				<sup style="margin:0pt 0pt 3pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;text-decoration:none;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;;"> (3)</sup>

Consolidated Financial Statements.)&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation applies the &#x201C;no negative number&#x201D; position for reporting the change in pension value.&nbsp;&nbsp;The fluctuations are primarily attributable to movement in the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">actuarial </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times 		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
				<sup style="margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;text-decoration:none;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;text-decoration:none;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;;"> (1)</sup>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:6pt 0pt 0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Bank has a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">legacy </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">SERP</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> for the CEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> that is explained in the &#x201C;PENSION BENEFIT</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#x201D; section of this proxy statement.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The CEO&#x2019;s participation in the legacy SERP began upon his</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> tenure as </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">CEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> the Corporation and the Bank in 2004.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except for this one legacy SERP, the Board has adopted a prohibition of tax gross-up arrangements and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> has</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> included this prohibition in the Corporation&#x2019;s published Corporate Governance Guidelines</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Compensation Committee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">believes that each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#x2019;s total compensation is appropriately balanced between currently paid out and deferred compensation, with deferred compensation consisting of equity awards that vest over time and retirement benefits provided under the Corporation&#x2019;s 401(k), Pension and SERP plans.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pay Ratio</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pursuant to Item 402(u) of Regulation S-K and Section 953(b) of the Dodd-Frank Act, presented below is the ratio of annual total compensation of the Corporation&#x2019;s CEO to the annual total compensation of the Corporation&#x2019;s median paid employee, excluding the CEO.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The ratio presented below is a reasonable estimate calculated in a manner consistent with Item 402(u).</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">T</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">he Corporation utilized the same median paid employee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">2017</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and 2018</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation believes </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">this </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">is appropriate because there have not been significant changes in the employee population</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> or compensation arrangements.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">In identifying the median paid employee in 2017 and in determining the compensation of the median paid employee in 2017 and 2018, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the Corporation utilized year-to-date compensation from the final (twenty-sixth) bi-weekly payroll of each year paid on December 22</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">nd</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and 21</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;font-size:5pt;vertical-align:super;line-height:100%">st</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ompensation included, as applicable, regular earnings plus overtime, Saturday pay, commissions, cash incentives and stock-based compensation.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;The Corporation considered all full-time and part-time permanent employees when identifying the median paid employee in 2017.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;E</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">arnings of employees included on </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">final </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">payroll </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">2017 </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">that were employed for less than a full year were converted to a twenty-six bi-weekly payroll equivalent. Full-time equivalent adjustments were not made.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> There were no seasonal or temporary employees on the final payroll of 2017.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> annual total compensation of our CEO and median paid employee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">was determined under Item 402 of Regulation S-K and was </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">$1,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">891</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">844</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">60</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">496</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, respectively.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO&#x2019;s annual total compensation for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> was </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">31</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> times that of the annual total compensation for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> of the median paid employee.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;This compares to 2017 annual total compensation of $1,669,209 and $59,360, respectively, and a 2017 pay ratio of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">28 times.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="CompensationPursuanttoPlans"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">COMPENSATION PURSUANT TO PLANS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;">Equity Incentive Plans </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Corporation has awards outstanding </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">u</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">nder the 2006 Stock Compensation Plan (&#x201C;2006 Plan&#x201D;) and the 2014 Plan.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Currently, a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">wards can only be granted under the 2014 Plan, which was approved by the Corporation&#x2019;s stockholders on April 22, 2014 as a successor to the 2006 Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 2014 Plan gives the Board flexibility to attract and retain highly qualified officers and directors by offering a competitive compensation program.&nbsp;&nbsp;Equity awards align the interests of our directors and management with the interests of our stockholders by potentially increasing the ownership interests of directors and officers in our </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ommon </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">tock.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Awards under the 2014 Plan may be granted as incentive and non-qualified stock options, stock appreciation rights, restricted stock awards, restricted stock units or any combination thereof.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ubstantially all awards granted under the 2014 Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> have bee</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">n restricted stock units with </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">performance or time-based vesting</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, while awards granted under the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> predecessor</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> plan </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">consisted of a combination of nonqualified stock options and restricted stock units</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The following table </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">presents </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the number of shares of Common Stock to be issued upon the exercise of outstanding stock options </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">vesting of RSUs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and the number of </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">shares of Common Stock </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">remaining available for future issuance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> under the 2014 Plan, as of December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, adjusted to reflect </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">107</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">511</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> RSUs granted in January 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">for </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;The table also presents the weighted average exercise price of outstanding stock options as of December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The following table sets forth information regarding the grant of plan-based awards</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, both cash and equity, to the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEOs</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font>

		<div style="width:100%"><table style="width:100%; table-layout: fixed;" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tr><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td valign="top" align="left" style="width: 18.00pt;">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<sup style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (1)</sup>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The actuarial assumptions used in determining the present value of the accumulated benefit for each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">under the Pension Plan are set forth in Note </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">J</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#x201C;Retirement Plans&#x201D; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">to the Corporation&#x2019;s 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">C</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">onsolidated </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">F</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">inancial </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">S</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">tatements.&nbsp;&nbsp;With respect to the SERP, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">the present value of the accumulated benefit is equal to the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">present value of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">annuity on </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">October 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pension Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Employees, including the NEOs, who are over 21 years of age and have been employed by the Bank for more than one year, are eligible to participate in the Pension Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Compensation used to determine benefits include</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> base salary, commissions, cash incentive compensation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> taxab</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">le fringe benefits, but excludes </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">employer contributions to the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, amounts realized from the exercise of nonqualified stock options, amounts realized from the conversion of restricted s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">tock units into shares of stock</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and amounts realized from the sale, exchange or other disposition of stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees that elect to participate in the Pens</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ion Plan make contributions of 2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">% &nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of their compensation used to determine benefits.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees become fully vested in the Pension Plan after 5 years of service with the Bank and 4 years of participation in the Pension Plan (no vesting occurs during that 5-year period) or, for employees hired before February 28, 2011, upon attainment of age 55.&nbsp;&nbsp;The normal retirement age is 65.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned through February 28, 2011, early retirement with an unreduced benefit is available at age 62, provided that at least 10 years of vesting service ha</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> been completed by age 62 and employment by the Bank began at age 55 or prior.&nbsp;&nbsp;Early retirement with a reduced benefit is available beginning at age 55.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned through February 28, 2011, the reduction is equal to 3% per year for each year that early retirement precedes age 65, or age 62 provided that at least 10 years of vesting service have been completed by age 62 and employment began at age 55 or prior.&nbsp;&nbsp;For benefits earned after February 28, 2011, the reduction is b</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">ased on actuarial equivalence.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Upon retirement, each participant with a spouse is paid a benefit in the form of a joint and survivor annuity.&nbsp;&nbsp;Participants without a spouse are paid a benefit in the form of a single life annuity guaranteed for sixty (60) months.&nbsp;&nbsp;All participants, whether with or without a spouse, may elect optional forms of benefit payments.&nbsp;&nbsp;For all participants, the annuity benefit is an amount equal to the sum</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of: (1) the participant&#x2019;s Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the product of 1.75 percent and the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service through February 28, 2011; plus (2) the participant&#x2019;s Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the product of 1.50 percent and the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service after February 28, 2011, with total years of credited service under clauses &#x201C;1&#x201D; and &#x201C;2&#x201D; limited to a maximum of 35 years; plus (3) 1.25 percent of Average Annual Compensation multiplied by the participant&#x2019;s credited years of service in excess of 35 years (up to five such years); and less (4) the product of .49 percent of the participant&#x2019;s Final Average Annual Compensation, limited to Covered Compensation, and the participant&#x2019;s Benefit Service up to 35 years.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 0.49 percent represents the minimum Social Security offset to the pension benefit.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> &nbsp;Average Annual Compensation, Final Average Annual Compensation, Covered Compensation and Benefit Service are all a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s defined in the Plan document.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Bank has a legacy SERP with the CEO as its only participant.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO&#x2019;s participation in this legacy plan began upon his </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">tenure </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">as CEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> the Corporation and the Bank in 2004.&nbsp;&nbsp;The SERP provides the additional benefits that would have been provided to</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> the CEO under the Pension </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> in the absence of Internal Revenue Code limitations for qualified plans. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The SERP was also designed so that the supplemental pension and </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">401(k) </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">contributions are made to a "secular trust" for the benefit of the CEO so that the assets are protected in the same manner as those of the Pension and 401(k) </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">P</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">lans (amounts contributed to the secular trust are not subject to the claims of creditors of the Bank).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank&#x2019;s contributions to the secular trust are tax-deductible by the Bank when made and, even though the SERP benefits will not be distributed to the CEO until a later time, such contributions and earnings thereon are taxable to the CEO when received or earned by the trust.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank&#x2019;s contributions to the SERP are reduced by applicable income tax withholdings.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a result of the foregoing, in lieu of increasing the Bank&#x2019;s contributions to the SERP or the CEOs other sources of compensation to take into account the taxes incurred by the CEO, the Bank contributes an amount to the SERP that, after applicable withholding taxes, will be sufficient to fund the SERP&#x2019;s benefit obligation when due.&nbsp;&nbsp;The assets in the secular trust are invested in equity and fixed income mutual funds, which produce earnings from dividends and interest.&nbsp;&nbsp;Except for this one legacy SERP </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">24</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;">arrangement, the Board of Directors has since adopted a prohibition of tax gross-up arrangements and included this prohibition in the Corporation&#x2019;s published Corporate Governance Guidelines.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The following table sets forth Nonqualified Deferred Compensation information as of and for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;">8</font><font style="display: inline;"> for Mr. Vittorio with respect to the supplemental </font><font style="display: inline;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;"> portion of the SERP.</font>
		</p>
