				<sup style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;font-family:Calibri;font-size:10pt;;"> (3)</sup>
			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Includes $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">469</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> previously reported as compensation to the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEO </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">in the Summary Compensation Tables for previous years.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
		<p style="margin:6pt 0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The Bank has a </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">tax-qualified </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">P</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">lan.&nbsp;&nbsp;Employees, including the NEOs, are eligible to participate provided they are at least 18 years of age.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Bank may, at its sole discretion, make matching contributions to each participant's account based on the amount of the participant's tax deferred contributions.&nbsp;&nbsp;Eligibility for employer matching contributions, if any, occurs after completing twelve (12) consecutive months of Eligibility Service, as defined, in which the participant worked a minimum of 1,000 hours.&nbsp;&nbsp;The sum of employee elective contributions and employer matching contributions plus any other additions to a participant&#x2019;s account </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">cannot exceed the lesser of $5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">,000 or 100% of the participant&#x2019;s compensation.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Participants are fully vested in their elective contributions and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> fully vest in any employer matching contributions </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">after five years of participation</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Employer matching contributions made during the first five years of participation vest ratably over the remainder of the five-year period.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Participants in the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> will receive benefits generally upon attainment of age 65.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) Plan</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> contains provisions allowing pre-termination withdrawals and loans under certain circumstances.&nbsp;&nbsp;The amount of a participant&#x2019;s Normal Retirement Benefit</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">, as defined,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> will depend upon the accumulation of contributions and forfeitures and the investment performance of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">401(k) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Plan.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 401(k) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Plan </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">matching contributions for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> made to the account</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> of each NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> are set forth in the &#x201C;All Other Compensation Table&#x201D; appearing elsewhere in this proxy statement.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="EmploymentAgreement"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">E</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">MPLOYMENT AGREEMENTS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">The NEOs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">each </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">have employment agreements with the Corporation pursuant to which Mr. Vittorio is employed as CEO of the Corporation, Mr. Curtis is employed as Senior Executive Vice President and CFO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of the Corporation, Mr. Becker is employed as Executive Vice President and Chief Risk Officer of the Corporation, Mr. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Hilton </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">is employed as Executive Vice President</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">of the Corporation </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">and Mr. Daley is employed as Executive Vice President and Senior Commercial Banking Officer of the Corporation.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Mr. Vittorio&#x2019;s employment agreement has a term of three (3) calendar years beginning January 1, 2017</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;"> and expiring on December 31, 2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Hilton&#x2019;s employment agreement has a term of two (2) calendar years beginning January 1, 2018 and the employment agreements with the other NEOs have terms of two (2) calendar years beginning January 1, 2017.&nbsp;&nbsp;Commencing on the first anniversary of each of these two-year employment agreements and continuing on each anniversary thereafter, each of these agreements shall renew for an additional period of one year such that the remaining term shall be two years unless written notice of non-renewal is provided to the NEO at least thirty (30) days prior to any such anniversary date.&nbsp;&nbsp;Notwithstanding the foregoing, each of these two-year employment agreements shall expire on December 31 of the calendar year in which the NEO attains age 65 (&#x201C;Retirement Age Termination Date&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Curtis&#x2019; employment agreement has been extended for two years beyond its Retirement Age Termination Date of December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing in these two-year employment agreements shall mandate or prohibit employment of the NEOs beyond their Retirement Age Termination Dates.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, a NEO shall not be entitled to any benefits or payments under his employment agreement following the Retirement Age Termination Date unless the Corporation has elected to extend such agreement pursuant to its terms for an additional period of two years.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">Pursuant to each NEO&#x2019;s employment agreement, if the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;color:#000000;">NEO is terminated by the Board without cause or the NEO terminates his employment following an event constituting Good Reason, the NEO will receive a cash lump sum severance payment equal to a multiple of the NEO&#x2019;s base salary (three times base salary for the CEO and two times base salary for the other NEOs) plus an amount equal to the product of the reasonably estimated monthly cost of the medical, dental and vision insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for the NEO immediately prior to the NEOs date of termination multiplied by thirty-six (36) for the CEO and twenty-four (24) for the other NEOs.&nbsp;&nbsp;The cash lump sum payment is conditioned on the NEO executing a release of the NEO&#x2019;s claims against the Corporation and </font>
		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">25</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">any affiliate, and their officers, directors, successors and assigns.&nbsp;&nbsp;The CEO&#x2019;s cash lump sum payment is also conditioned on the CEO not being eligible to receive compensation and benefits pursuant to the CEO&#x2019;s employment agreement in connection with a change in control</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, as defined</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to receiving a cash lump sum payment, outstanding restricted stock units granted to the CEO shall become vested and payable under the same terms and conditions as would apply upon the CEO&#x2019;s retirement as set forth in the applicable award agreements between the Corporation and the CEO.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Upon termination of the CEO&#x2019;s employment by the Corporation without cause or by the CEO with Good Reason on or after the effective time of a change in control, as defined, the CEO shall receive a cash lump sum payment equal to three (3) times the sum of CEOs highest rate of base salary payable during the current calendar year of the CEO&#x2019;s date of termination or either of the two (2) calendar years immediately preceding the CEO&#x2019;s date of termination. In addition, the CEO shall receive a cash lump sum equal to thirty-six (36) times the reasonably estimated monthly cost of the medical, dental and vision insurance coverage maintained by the Bank for CEO immediately prior to the CEO&#x2019;s date of termination.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the case of the other NEOs, termination of employment by the Corporation without cause or by the NEO with Good Reason after the effective time of a change in control, as defined, results in the same severance payment that would be made in the absence of a change in control.&nbsp;&nbsp;In the event of a change in control, and pursuant to the terms of the award agreements between the NEOs and the Corporation, all outstanding and unvested equity awards shall immediately vest. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Good Reason exists if, without the NEO&#x2019;s express written consent, any of the following occurs: (i) the failure to appoint the NEO during the term of the NEOs employment agreement to the executive position occupied by the NEO at the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> date of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> commencement of the employment agreement; (ii) a reduction in the NEO&#x2019;s base salary; (iii) the failure of the Bank to maintain the NEO&#x2019;s participation under the Bank&#x2019;s employee benefit, retirement, or material fringe benefit plans, policies, practices, or arrangements in which the NEO participates; or (iv) a relocation of the NEO&#x2019;s principal place of employment by more than 50 miles from the NEO&#x2019;s principal place of employment at the</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> date of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> commencement of the NEO&#x2019;s employment agreement.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Notwithstanding the foregoing,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the change in control severance payments under the employment agreements for the NEOs will be reduced to avoid an excess parachute payment under Section 280G of the Internal Revenue Code if doing so results in a greater after-tax benefit to the NEO</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Each NEO&#x2019;s employment agreement subjects the NEO to non-compete and non-solicitation provisions</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for a period of two years for the CEO or one year for the other NEOs following their date of termination, provided, however, that such restrictions would not apply in the event of the NEOs termination for cause or termination of employment following a change in control</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The following table sets forth potential payments to the NEOs upon termination of their employment by the Corporation without cause or by the NEOs for Good Reason absent a change in control.&nbsp;&nbsp;The table also sets forth for the NEOs the accelerated vesting, if any, of unvested option and stock awards.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 11pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="TransactionsWithMgmtandOthers"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">TRANSACTIONS WITH MANAGEMENT AND OTHERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines require the Board to conduct an appropriate review of all related party transactions for potential conflict of interest situations.&nbsp;&nbsp;Related party transactions are those required to be disclosed pursuant to Item 404 of Regulation S-K.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Board fulfills the requirement to review related party transactions in conjunction with the Audit Committee, which is comprised entirely of independent directors.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Governance and Nominating Committee is charged with the responsibility of reviewing and assessing the adequacy of and compliance with the Corporation&#x2019;s Corporate Governance Guidelines and recommending any proposed changes to the Board for approval.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="_Hlk536695321"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In 1992, the Bank, as tenant, entered into a lease with H. T. Hogan Jr., d/b/a Briar Ridge Properties, covering premises in a building located in Locust Valley, New York, used as a branch office. </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> The Bank subsequently modified and extended the lease in 2002 and 2012.&nbsp;&nbsp;The 2012 modification and extension</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">including the current </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">five-year</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> renewal period</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> expires on </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">October 31, 20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">22</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition to base rent, the Bank is responsible for its proportionate share of the real estate taxes on the building in which the leased premises are located.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the terms of the lease, the Bank was obligated to pay $4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">4</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">38</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;In 2009, the Bank, as tenant, entered into a lease with CSH Realty LLC, covering premises in a building located in Cold Spring Harbor, New York used as a branch office.&nbsp;&nbsp;The lease expires on December 31, 2019.&nbsp;&nbsp;Under the terms of the lease, the Bank was obligated to pay $33,014 for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;Howard Thomas Hogan, Jr., a director of the Corporation and the Bank</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, owns</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">or controls companies that own </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">both properties.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Corporation believes that the terms of the leases are comparable to competitive terms that could have been obtained from an unrelated third party.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Bank has had, and expects to have in the future, banking transactions in the ordinary course of its business with directors, executive officers, principal stockholders of the Corporation and their associates.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such transactions, including borrowings and loan commitments, are made in the ordinary course of business on substantially the same terms, including interest rates and collateral, as</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">those prevailing at the time for compa</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">rable transactions with others </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> in the opinion of management</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> do not involve more than a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> normal risk of collectability </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">nor do they present other unfavorable features.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Certain directors are officers, directors, partners or stockholders of companies or partnerships which, or associates of which, may have been customers of the Bank in the ordinary course of business during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and up to the present time.&nbsp;&nbsp;Additional transactions of this type may occur in the future.&nbsp;&nbsp;All such transactions were effected on substantially the same terms as comparable transactions with other persons.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="Section16A"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">SECTION&nbsp;16(A) BENEFICIAL OWNERSHIP REPORTING COMPLIANCE</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Our executive officers</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> directors and beneficial owners of greater than 10% of the outstanding shares of Common Stock are required to file reports with the SEC</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">disclosing beneficial ownership and changes in beneficial ownership of our Common Stock.&nbsp;&nbsp;SEC</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">rules require disclosure if an executive officer, director or 10% beneficial owner does not file these reports on a timely basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Based on our review of ownership reports required to be filed for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, all filing requirements were satisfied</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> on a timely basis</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>

			<a name="Proposal3AppointmentofPublicAcctFirm"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PROPOSAL </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">3</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">RATIFICATION OF APPOINTMENT OF INDEPENDENT REGISTERED</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">PUBLIC ACCOUNTING FIRM</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The consolidated financial statements of the Corporation for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> were audited by Crowe LLP (&#x201C;Crowe&#x201D;).&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee has appointed Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm to audit the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements for the year ending December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp;&nbsp;A resolution will be presented at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders to ratify the appointment of Crowe.&nbsp;&nbsp;The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of shares represented in person or by proxy and voting on this item will be required for ratification.&nbsp;&nbsp;If there is no designation on an executed proxy as to how the shares represented should be voted, the proxy will be voted for the ratification.&nbsp;&nbsp;If the stockholders do not ratify the appointment of Crowe, the Audit Committee will reconsider its selection of Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even if the stockholders ratify the appointment of Crowe, the Audit Committee in its discretion may direct the appointment of a different independent registered public accounting firm </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">at any time during the year if it determines that such change is in the best interests of the Corporation and its stockholders.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">A representative of Crowe </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">is expected to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">be present at the Annual Meeting of Stockholders and will have the opportunity to make a statement and respond to appropriate questions from stockholders.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">The Board of Directors recommends a vote FOR ratification of the appointment of Crowe as the Corporation&#x2019;s independent registered public accounting firm.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Fees </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Crowe</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&#x2019;s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> fees for audit services for 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> were $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">30</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">00</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0 and $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">2</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">70</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">00</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0, respectively.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The increase in audit fees is mainly due to the Corporation&#x2019;s continued growth and expansion.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Audit services include the following: (1) professional services rendered for the audit of the Corporation&#x2019;s annual consolidated financial statements; (2) reviews of the consolidated financial statements</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> included in the Corporation&#x2019;s Quarterly R</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eports on Form 10-Q; (3) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a reading of the Corporation&#x2019;s Annual R</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eport on Form 10-K; and (4) rendering an opinion on the effectiveness of the Corporation&#x2019;s internal control over financial reporting.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Related Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Audit related fees, as described in Item 9(e)(2) of Schedule 14A of the SEC&#x2019;s Proxy Rules, are fees billed to the Corporation by its </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Independent Registered Public Accounting Firm (&#x201C;Independent Auditors&#x201D;)</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for assurance and related services that are reasonably related to the performance of the audit or review of the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements and are not audit fees as described in the previous paragraph.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, Crowe did not bill the Corporation for any audit related fees.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Cambria;color:#243F60;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">Tax Fees </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Crowe&#x2019;s fees in 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> for preparing the Corporation&#x2019;s tax returns, providing tax advice and performing tax compliance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> work were $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">3</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">0</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">00</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and $</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">29</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">,</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">500</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, respectively.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp;Crowe&#x2019;s fees in 2018 for other tax-related work, mainly the completion of a cost segregation study relating to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">accelerated </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">tax depreciation, were $78,825.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Cambria;color:#243F60;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;color:#000000;font-size:10pt;">All Other Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In neither of the last two fiscal years was the Corporation billed by Crowe for any fees other than those described above under the captions &#x201C;Audit Fees,&#x201D; &#x201C;Audit Related Fees&#x201D; and &#x201C;Tax Fees.&#x201D;</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Audit Committee Approval of Audit Related, Tax and Other Fees</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">7</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the Audit Committee specifically approved or pre-approved all fees reported under the sections &#x201C;Audit Related Fees&#x201D; and &#x201C;Tax Fees.&#x201D;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Engagement of Independent Auditors to Perform Audit Services and Non-Audit Services</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">On an annual basis, and in accordance with the terms of written engagement letters, the Audit Committee </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">has </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">engage</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">d</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors to perform audit services as previously defined and to prepare the Corporation&#x2019;s income tax returns. </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">In addition, from time to time the Audit Committee may engage the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors to perform non-audit services such as providing tax advice and performing tax compliance work.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee has pre-approved specific types of non-audit services provided that the cost of such services does not exceed $50,000 in any calendar year.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee will not engage the Independent Auditors to perform any non-audit service or pre-approve any non-audit service that could impair, in fact or appearance, the independence of the Independent Auditors.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, the Audit Committee will not pre-approve any non-audit service if such pre-approval constitutes delegation to management of the Audit Committee&#x2019;s responsibilities under the 1934</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Act</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;font-size: 10pt">

		</p>
		<p><font size="1"> </font></p><div style="width:100%">

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">

			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">28</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt;text-align:center;line-height:100%;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 11pt">

			&nbsp;

		</p>

</div><hr size="3" style="color:#999999" width="100%" align="center"></hr><p style="page-break-after:always">&nbsp;</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 10pt;font-family:Calibri;line-height:115%;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"></font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="AuditCommitteeReport"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">AUDIT COMMITTEE REPORT</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Under its charter, the Audit Committee is responsible to assist the Board in fulfilling its oversight responsibilities by reviewing and evaluating: 1) the qualifications and independence of the Independent Auditors; 2) the performance of the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, i</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">nternal audit function</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and vendors providing internal auditing services</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">; 3) the integrity of the Corporation&#x2019;s financial statements; and 4) management&#x2019;s responsibilities to assure that there is in place an effective system of internal controls.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">While the Audit Committee has the responsibilities and powers set forth in this Charter, it is not the duty of the Audit Committee to plan or conduct audits or to determine that the Corporation&#x2019;s financial statements and disclosures are complete and accurate and are in accordance with Generally Accepted Accounting Principles (&#x201C;GAAP&#x201D;) and applicable rules and regulations.&nbsp;&nbsp;These are the responsibilities of management and the Independent Auditors.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Specific duties and responsibilities of the Audit Committee include, among other things:</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> 1) appoint, retain, compensate, evaluate and, where appropriate, replace the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Independent Auditors;&nbsp;&nbsp;2) </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">approve all fees and terms of engagement of the Independent Auditors; 3) confirm the independence of the Independent Auditors; 4) review and discuss with management and the Independent Auditors the Corporation&#x2019;s audited consolidated financial statements and internal control over financial reporting; 5) meet with the Corporation&#x2019;s Independent Auditors and review the scope of audit services and the results of their annual audit of the Corporation&#x2019;s consolidated financial statements, including any recommendations the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Independent A</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">uditors may have with respect to internal controls or other business matters; 6) approve the internal audit plan and review the scope and results of internal audits; 7) review the results of examinations performed by regulatory authorities; 8) oversee management&#x2019;s responsibility to fulfill the annual internal control reporting requirements of Section 404 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act and the annual audit and management reporting requirements of the Federal Deposit Insurance Corporation Improvement Act of 1991; 9) review the Bank's performance of its obligations under various laws and regulations, including those affecting consumers; 10) review </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">related party transactions; and 11) oversee management&#x2019;s responsibility to implement internal controls over information technology </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and information security </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">risk</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">. &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The evaluation of the Independent Auditors </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">occurs at least annually and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">includes, among other things, a review of the most recent Public Company Accounting Oversight Board (&#x201C;PCAOB&#x201D;) report and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">communications required by PCAOB Auditing Standard Number 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">301</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> regarding the independence and appointment of the Independent Auditors and the results of the annual audit.&nbsp;&nbsp;The evaluation also includes consideration of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Independent Auditors </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">qualifications</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">industry experience</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">performance</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> of the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">udit </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">p</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">artner and audit team</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and the tenure </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">of the firm </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">and appropriateness of fees</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Crowe has served as the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Corporation&#x2019;s I</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ndependent </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">A</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">uditor</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">s</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> since 2003 and the audit partner is rotated at least every five years.&nbsp; </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Audit Committee received and reviewed the written disclosures and the letter from Crowe required by applicable requirements of the PCAOB regarding Crowe&#x2019;s communications with the Audit Committee concerning independence, and discussed with Crowe their independence.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Audit Committee reviews and discusses with management and the Independent Auditors the annual audited financial statements, </font><font style="display: inline;">the Annual Report on </font><font style="display: inline;">Form 10-K, </font><font style="display: inline;">Quarterly Reports on </font><font style="display: inline;">Form 10-Q</font><font style="display: inline;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;">and earnings press releases prior to their filing, including reviewing the disclosures made in "Management's Discussion and Analysis of Financial Condition and Results of Operation</font><font style="display: inline;">s</font><font style="display: inline;">."&nbsp;&nbsp;The Audit Committee also reviews and d</font><font style="display: inline;">iscusses policies with respect to risk assessment and risk management.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such discussions include the Corporation&#x2019;s major financial and accounting risk exposures and the steps management has undertaken to control them</font><font style="display: inline;font-style:italic;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Audit Committee reviews reports from management regarding, among other things, the framework and effectiveness of internal controls over financial reporting</font><font style="display: inline;"> and disclosure controls</font><font style="display: inline;">, compliance with laws and regulations, and controls over information technology risk</font><font style="display: inline;">.</font><font style="display: inline;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;background-color: #FFFFFF;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Audit Committee met </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eight </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">times during 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> and schedules meetings to ensure it devotes enough time and attention to the duties and responsibilities outlined in this report.&nbsp;&nbsp;Periodic executive sessions are held with the Independent Auditors, Chief Auditor and other members of management to discuss any matters that the Committee or these persons believe should be discussed.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Audit Committee regularly reports its activities to the Board, and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">annually </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">conducts a review of its Charter and </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">performs </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">a self-assessment.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">Based on the review and discussions referred to above, we recommended to the Board that the audited financial statements be included in the Corporation&#x2019;s Annual Report on Form 10-K for the year ended December 31, 201</font><font style="display: inline;">8</font><font style="display: inline;"> for filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;text-indent:0pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;">The Audit Committee:</font>
		</p>

			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
				<font style="margin:0pt;font-family:Symbol;font-size:11pt;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;;"> &#xB7;</font>

			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">
			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">John J. Desmond</font></p></td></tr></table></div>

			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">

			</p>
		</td><td style="width:0pt;"><p style="width:0pt;width:0pt;font-size:0pt;"></p></td><td align="left" valign="top">
			<p style="border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size: 10pt;margin:0pt;">

			<font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">The preceding report shall not be deemed incorporated by reference by any general statement incorporating by reference this proxy statement into any filing under the 1933 Act</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">&nbsp;</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">or </font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">1</font><font style="display: inline;color:#000000;">934 Act, except to the extent the Corporation specifically incorporates this information by reference, and shall not otherwise be deemed filed under the 1933 Act or the 1934 Act.</font>

		</p>

		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;;font-size: 10pt"><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">OTHER MATTERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Board of the Corporation does not know of any matters for action by stockholders at the Annual Meeting other than the matters described in the Notice of Annual Meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;However, the enclosed Proxy will confer discretionary authority with respect to matters which are not known to the Board at the time of the printing hereof and which may properly come before the meeting.&nbsp;&nbsp;It is the intention of the persons named in the </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">p</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">roxy to vote such </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">p</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">roxy with respect to such matters in accordance with their best judgment.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The entire expense of preparing, assembling and mailing the enclosed material will be borne by the Corporation.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition to using the mail, directors, officers and employees of the Bank acting on behalf of the Corporation, and without extra compensation, may solicit proxies in person, by telephone</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">by facsimile.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="StckhldrsProposals"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSALS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Any proposals of stockholders intended to be submitted at the 20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting of Stockholders under SEC Rule 14a-8 must be received by the Chairman of the Board or the President no later than November 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">5</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> in order to be considered for inclusion in the proxy statement and form of proxy for such meeting under SEC Rule 14a-8.&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Under the Corporation&#x2019;s bylaws, a stockholder must follow certain procedures to nominate persons for election as directors or to introduce an item of business at a meeting of stockholders. These procedures provide, generally, that stockholders desiring to make nominations for directors, or to bring a proper subject of business before the 20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting, must do so by a written notice timely delivered to the Corporation&#x2019;s Secretary generally not later than December 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">If the Corporation is not notified of a matter to be brought before the 20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">20</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting by December 1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> or if a matter is omitted from the proxy statement or proxy pursuant to SEC Rule 14a-8, then the proxy may provide discretionary authority to management of the Corporation to vote against such matter.&nbsp;&nbsp; </font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Nothing in this proxy statement will be deemed to require us to include in our proxy statement and proxy relating to an annual meeting any stockholder proposal that does not meet all of the requirements for inclusion established by the SEC in effect at the time such proposal is received.</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> &nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="InternetAvailability"></a><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">INTERNET AVAILABILITY OF PROXY MATERIALS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-bottom:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Important Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials for the Annual Meeting of</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> Stockholders to be held on</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> April </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">1</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">6</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">, 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">9</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;border-top:1pt none #D9D9D9 ;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">&#xFEFF;</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Company&#x2019;s proxy statement and form of proxy for its 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">9</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Meeting of Stockholders and its 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"> Annual R</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">eport on Form 10-K to security holders is available at </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">ht</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">tp://www.cstproxy.com/fnbli/2019</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">For driving directions to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">North Hempstead Country Club</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">, the location of the annual meeting, please go to </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">https://www.nhccli.com</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">.</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:center;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size: 10pt">
			<a name="AnnualRpttoStckhldrs"></a><font style="display: inline;">ANNUAL REPORTS TO STOCKHOLDERS</font>
		</p>
		<p style="margin:0pt 0pt 6pt;line-height:100%;text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph;font-family:Calibri;font-size: 10pt">
			<font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Consolidated financial statements for the Corporation are included in the Corporation&#x2019;s 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Report on Form 10-K which was mailed with this Proxy Statement.&nbsp;&nbsp;In addition, copies of the 201</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">8</font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;"> Annual Report on Form 10-K as filed with the Securities and Exchange Commission will be sent to any stockholder upon written request without charge.&nbsp;&nbsp;Such request should be directed to Mark D. Curtis, </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Senior </font><font style="display: inline;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;">Executive Vice President, Chief Financial Officer and Treasurer, at the Corporation&#x2019;s principal office, 10 Glen Head Road, Glen Head, New York 11545.</font>
